<paragraph id="2418850BFF9B836BFF485C64FD1FFB47" blockId="38.[112,766,1028,1468]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF9B836BFF485C64FF5BFBE0" box="[140,203,1028,1051]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="38">Notes.</emphasis>
– Both duplicates at 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFE625C64FE26FBE0" box="[422,438,1028,1051]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
have the catalogue (not collection) number 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF9B836BFEC65C44FEA6FBC7" box="[258,310,1060,1084]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="38">1442</emphasis>
. The single material that Boissier examined for the species description was 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFE745C24FE2EFBA7" box="[432,446,1092,1116]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
<date id="5019A3CBFF9B836BFE795C24FDB3FBA7" box="[445,547,1092,1116]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" value="2710-02-27">02272710</date>
, which he annotated and from which he took a fragment consisting of an upper cauline leaf and three flowering tips. He did not annotate 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFFB75CC4FF11FB47" box="[115,129,1188,1212]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
<date id="5019A3CBFF9B836BFF455CC4FF79FB47" box="[129,233,1188,1212]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" value="2709-02-27">02272709</date>
and, most certainly did not examine it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF9B836BFF485CA4FD6EFA47" blockId="38.[112,766,1028,1468]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38">
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF9B836BFF485CA4FED7FB27" author="JAFRI, S. M. H." box="[140,327,1220,1244]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" pagination="55" refId="ref140019" refString="JAFRI, S. M. H. (1973). Brassicaceae. In: NASIR, E. &amp; S. I. ALI (ed.), Fl. W. Pakistan 55." type="book chapter" year="1973">JAFRI (1973: 234)</bibRefCitation>
arbitrarily indicated that the type is at 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFFB75C84FF1AFB07" box="[115,138,1252,1276]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
, though he did not examine nor annotate it. By contrast, 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF9B836BFFB65D64FEEBFAE0" author="POLATSCHEK, A." box="[114,379,1283,1308]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" pagination="181 - 275" refId="ref142424" refString="POLATSCHEK, A. (2010). Revision der Gattung Erysimum (Cruciferae): Teil 1: Russland, die Nachfolgestaaten der USSR (excl. Georgien, Armenien, Azerbaidzan), China, Indien, Pakistan, Japan und Korea. Ann. Naturhist. Mus. Wien, B 111: 181 - 275." type="journal article" year="2010">POLATSCHEK (2010: 251)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFE385D64FD9AFAE7" box="[508,522,1284,1308]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
<date id="5019A3CBFF9B836BFDCD5D64FDE1FAE7" box="[521,625,1284,1308]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" value="2709-02-27">02272709</date>
as the 
<typeStatus id="FB1C3BA9FF9B836BFD7B5D64FF31FAC7" pageId="38" pageNumber="38">lectotype</typeStatus>
, and one of us (IAS) erroneously annotated it in 2016 as such. However, that sheet is less complete and does not show the inflated and thickened stem as does 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFDA05D04FDE2FA87" box="[612,626,1380,1404]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
<date id="5019A3CBFF9B836BFDB65D04FD4AFA87" box="[626,730,1380,1404]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" value="2710-02-27">02272710</date>
. In our opinion, no lectotypification is necessary, and 
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF9B836BFD4E5DE4FD07FA67" box="[650,663,1412,1436]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
<date id="5019A3CBFF9B836BFD535DE4FD6CFA67" box="[663,764,1412,1436]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" value="2710-02-27">02272710</date>
ought to be considered as the 
<typeStatus id="FB1C3BA9FF9B836BFE765DC4FD80FA47" box="[434,528,1444,1468]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38">holotype</typeStatus>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF9B836BFD835DC4FD63FA47" author="BOISSIER, E." box="[583,755,1444,1468]" pageId="38" pageNumber="38" pagination="347 - 377" refId="ref136000" refString="BOISSIER, E. (1841 a). Plantae Aucherianae orientales enumeratae, cum novarum specierum descriptione. Ann. Sci. Nat., Bot. ser. 2, 16: 347 - 377." type="journal article" year="1841">BOISSIER, 1841a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
